JavaScript and jQuery based single line typing_effect

You need to include the typing-effect.js in html page and define an empty dom element such as div with id defined.


then use typing_effect('This is a sample string for testing single line typing effect!', '#typing_line', true); in either script tag or your .js file

first parameter: string to be used for typing effect
second parameter: id of the dom element
third parameter: true, if you want to earse as well after a little pause, false: if you want to keep it after typing complete

